{
  "name": "Warding Wind",
  "type": "spell",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>A strong wind (20 miles per hour) blows around you in a 10-foot radius and moves with you, remaining centered on you. The wind lasts for the spell's duration.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>The wind has the following effects:</p><ul class=\"rd__list\"><li class=\"rd__li \">It @condition[deafened||deafens] you and other creatures in its area.</li><li class=\"rd__li \">It extinguishes unprotected flames in its area that are torch-sized or smaller.</li><li class=\"rd__li \">It hedges out vapor, gas, and fog that can be dispersed by strong wind.</li><li class=\"rd__li \">The area is difficult terrain for creatures other than you.</li><li class=\"rd__li \">The attack rolls of ranged weapon attacks have disadvantage if the attacks pass in or out of the wind.</li></ul></div>",
